<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Character homes and consistent family demand.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Norman Park is a firm favourite with families seeking inner-east character living. Wide streets, heritage Queenslanders, good schools and easy access to the CBD and river create consistent, strong demand from buyers who know exactly what they want.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I have sold extensively in Norman Park and understand the nuances that separate a good result from an exceptional one. The right preparation and buyer targeting makes a real difference in a suburb this tightly held.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Old Cleveland Road runs through the suburb's heart and provides easy bus access to the CBD, which is a genuine factor in buyer decision-making for young families and professionals alike. Norman Creek and the adjoining parkland create a natural green buffer along the western edge, and homes backing onto that reserve attract a premium from buyers who understand the land value of such proximity. Seven Hills Bushland Reserve to the south adds to the suburb's green credentials. Character home demand in Norman Park remains robust, with original Queenslanders drawing strong auction competition from buyers who have been outpriced in Hawthorne and Balmoral.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Norman Park Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Inner East Brisbane</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Character Suburb</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Strong family demand</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:#78716c;margin-top:2rem;">Also selling in: <a href="/suburbs/hawthorne" style="color:#c4912a;">Hawthorne</a>, <a href="/suburbs/camp-hill" style="color:#c4912a;">Camp Hill</a>, <a href="/suburbs/east-brisbane" style="color:#c4912a;">East Brisbane</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

